Others: Pakistan won the toss and chose to bowl first in the third T20I against Ireland in Dublin.
Ireland have kept the run-scoring tempo up against Pakistan, piling on 125 runs for the loss of two wickets after 12.5 overs.
Pakistan need 23 more runs off five overs, with eight wickets still in hand against Ireland.
Pakistan win with ease, chasing down Ireland's target of 179 runs with six wickets and 18 balls to spare, clinching the series by a 2-1 margin.
